---
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
// B-NEW-13: shared single source of truth.
import { LEGAL_VERSIONS, LEGAL_LAST_UPDATED_LABEL } from "@/config/legal-versions";
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Acceptable Use Policy — MotionMax"
  description="MotionMax acceptable use policy. Understand the permitted and prohibited uses of our AI video generation platform."
  canonical="https://motionmax.io/acceptable-use"
  documentVersion={LEGAL_VERSIONS.aup}
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-2">Acceptable Use Policy</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-10">
    Version <span class="font-mono">{LEGAL_VERSIONS.aup}</span> &nbsp;·&nbsp; Last updated: {LEGAL_LAST_UPDATED_LABEL}
  </p>

  <div class="space-y-8 text-muted-foreground">

    {/* C-13-8 / Tongue TONGUE-11: English-only disclosure. */}
    <section class="rounded-md border border-border/40 bg-muted/20 p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed">
      This document is provided in English. We are working to translate it into additional languages.
      If you do not understand any provision, please contact us at
      <a href="mailto:support@motionmax.io" class="text-primary hover:underline">support@motionmax.io</a>
      for clarification before using the Service.
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">1. Overview</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">MotionMax provides AI-powered video, image, and voice generation tools. By using our platform, you agree to use it responsibly and in accordance with this Acceptable Use Policy ("AUP"). Violations may result in account suspension or termination.</p>
    </section>

    {/* C-13-2 (Comply L-C-02): consent-based synthetic-media rules
        replace the previous categorical "no deepfakes" ban that
        contradicted the product itself. */}
    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">2. Prohibited Uses</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">You may NOT use the Service to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Generate synthetic media (image, voice, or video) depicting any identifiable person without their explicit prior consent.</li>
        <li>Create content intended to deceive viewers into believing it depicts real events that did not occur.</li>
        <li>Impersonate any identified person in commercial, political, or otherwise public-facing communications without their consent.</li>
        <li>Produce content that is illegal, harmful, threatening, abusive, harassing, or defamatory.</li>
        <li>Infringe the intellectual property rights of any third party.</li>
        <li>Generate explicit, pornographic, or sexually explicit material — including non-consensual intimate imagery of any kind.</li>
        <li>Promote violence, terrorism, or self-harm; produce content depicting minors in unsafe contexts.</li>
        <li>Spread disinformation or manipulated media designed to mislead a public audience without clear AI-generated disclosure.</li>
        <li>Violate the privacy of any individual, or target / harass specific individuals or groups.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">2.1 Voice Cloning Consent</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">You represent that you have explicit consent from any voice owner before cloning their voice on the Service. Voice cloning of public figures, deceased persons, or any individual without their consent is strictly prohibited and is grounds for immediate termination. Where applicable jurisdictions classify voice recordings as biometric identifiers (Illinois BIPA, Texas CUBI, California CPRA, and similar laws), you further acknowledge that consent must be in writing and that the voice owner retains the right to withdraw consent and request deletion of their biometric data at any time.</p>
    </section>

    {/* Wave E-Legal Part D: AUP minimum-age clause. Mirrors the React
        AUP §2.2 — the 18+ rule already lives in ToS §3 but restating it
        here gives the AUP its own self-contained age gate. */}
    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">2.2 Minimum Age</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">You must be at least 18 years of age to create an account or use the Service. We do not knowingly allow access by anyone under 18, and in particular do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 (United States COPPA threshold) or under the higher local age-of-digital-consent threshold where it applies (e.g. 16 in Germany under GDPR Art. 8). If we learn that a user is under the applicable minimum age, we will close the account and delete personal information. Parents or guardians who believe a minor has registered may contact <a href="mailto:privacy@motionmax.io" class="text-primary hover:underline">privacy@motionmax.io</a> for immediate removal.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">3. Voice Cloning — Practical Use</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">The voice cloning feature requires your explicit consent and must only be used with voices you have the legal right to clone. Cloning another person's voice without their explicit written consent is strictly prohibited and may constitute a violation of applicable laws, including those related to fraud, identity theft, and defamation.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">4. Commercial Use</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">Commercial use of generated videos is permitted under paid plans. You are responsible for ensuring that content you distribute commercially complies with all applicable laws and does not infringe third-party rights.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">5. API &amp; Automation</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">Automated access, scraping, or reverse engineering of MotionMax's systems is prohibited without explicit written permission. Rate limits must be respected at all times.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">6. Enforcement</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">We reserve the right to remove content, suspend, or permanently terminate accounts that violate this policy, without prior notice. Repeated violations will result in permanent bans without refund.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">7. Reporting Violations</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">To report a violation of this policy, contact us at <a href="mailto:abuse@motionmax.io" class="text-primary hover:underline">abuse@motionmax.io</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="border-t border-border/30 pt-6 text-center">
      <p class="text-sm">
        Questions? <a href="mailto:support@motionmax.io" class="text-primary hover:underline">Contact us</a>
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <a href="/terms" class="text-primary hover:underline">Terms</a>
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <a href="/privacy" class="text-primary hover:underline">Privacy</a>
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</LegalLayout>
